"{\"uid\": \"cityam.com-team-gb-add-to-velodrome-medal-haul-at-paris-2024-olympic-games\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 45, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 47, \"to\": 92, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 94, \"to\": 139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By:Matt Hardy  Deputy Sports Editor - City AM  Team GB picked up a pair of minor medals at thevelodrome on Wednesdayas their wait to add to their day one gold goes on.\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 308, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 144, \"end\": 154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Hardy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matt Hardy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Hardy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Hardy\"}, {\"begin\": 188, \"end\": 195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.5729923674437706, \"rank\": 0.5042888777752471, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's team pursuit outfit - made up of Ethan Hayter, Dan Bigham, Charlie Tanfield and Ethan Vernon, plus fifth rider Ollie Wood - picked up a silver in their final against Australia.\", \"from\": 310, \"to\": 496, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 353, \"end\": 365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Hayter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ethan Hayter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Hayter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Hayter\"}, {\"begin\": 379, \"end\": 395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlie_Tanfield\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charlie Tanfield\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlie_Tanfield\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlie_Tanfield\"}, {\"begin\": 400, \"end\": 412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Vernon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ethan Vernon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Vernon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Vernon\"}, {\"begin\": 486, \"end\": 495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.52455968359787, \"rank\": 0.820540995078022, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Brits looked to be clawing back against the strong favourites Australia but Hayter fell off his saddle.\", \"from\": 497, \"to\": 604, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 497, \"end\": 506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brit_Awards\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Brits\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brit_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brit_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 563, \"end\": 572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.52455968359787, \"rank\": 0.820540995078022, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 577, \"end\": 583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanley_William_Hayter\", \"score\": 0.9953964083944206, \"rank\": 0.004624882193230358, \"text\": \"Hayter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanley_William_Hayter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanley_William_Hayter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB cyclist Hayter said: \\\"I had the race in my hands and I tied up and went deep.\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 691, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 622, \"end\": 628, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanley_William_Hayter\", \"score\": 0.9953964083944206, \"rank\": 0.004624882193230358, \"text\": \"Hayter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanley_William_Hayter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanley_William_Hayter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We took it to them but we could have paced it a little better.\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 754, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We left it out there.\", \"from\": 756, \"to\": 778, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a bit embarrassing [to come off the seat].\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 826, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bigham added: \\\"I was bloody nervous, the start was killing me.\", \"from\": 828, \"to\": 890, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We were riding damn well and we leaned on [Ethan] a lot and we probably gave him half-a-lap too long.\\\"\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 993, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stay in the game with The Turnover: your weekly roundup of sport business news, expert analysis and behind\\u2011the\\u2011scenes stories from City\\u202fAM's sports desk.\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1148, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"An hour later Team GB's women's side picked up bronze, coming from a second down against Italy to win by nearly two seconds in their race for third.\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1298, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1164, \"end\": 1171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.5729923674437706, \"rank\": 0.5042888777752471, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The two medals add to the gold from the women's team sprint and silver from the men's team pursuit.\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1399, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Today at Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines Velodrome there will be medals handed out in the women's keirin and the men's omnium.\", \"from\": 1401, \"to\": 1521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1493, \"end\": 1499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.754880326295761e-45, \"text\": \"keirin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Emma Finucane and Katy Marchant go for Team GB in the quarter-finals from 4:18pm.\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1604, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1523, \"end\": 1527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"score\": 0.9999995965027569, \"rank\": 3.46760177222805e-07, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\"}, {\"begin\": 1541, \"end\": 1554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katy Marchant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hayter and Wood, part of Wednesday's team pursuit silver medal, will compete in the men's omnium - Matthew Walls of Great Britain won this event in Tokyo three days ago.\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1775, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1705, \"end\": 1718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Walls\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matthew Walls\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Walls\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Walls\"}, {\"begin\": 1722, \"end\": 1735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999928229204382, \"rank\": 7.0179023993071605e-06, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1754, \"end\": 1759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999464805753064, \"rank\": 4.8305438710033666e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cycling will continue at Paris 2024 until Sunday.\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1826, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Share this article  Subscribe to the City AM newsletter to have our top stories delivered directly to your inbox.\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 1941, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow us for breaking news and latest updates\", \"from\": 1943, \"to\": 1989, \"entities\": []}]}"